Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Spread the @McCain Home Chips{400%grams} on a #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle
with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Bake on the top shelf, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%grams}.

Cut the @Medium Tomato{1} into 2cm chunks.

Put the @Cider Vinegar{15%ml} in a #medium bowl{} with the @Sugar{1/2%tsp} and
@Olive Oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then mix
together.

Add the tomatoes to the dressing and mix again, then set aside.

When the chips have 12 mins remaining, place the @Unconventional Plant-Based Burgers{2}
on a large, lightly oiled baking tray.

Bake on the middle shelf until browned, ~{8-9%minutes}.

Once the burgers are cooked, remove from the oven and place the cheese on top of
them. Put the @Burger Buns{2} on the same baking tray.

Return to the middle shelf of your oven until the cheese is melted and the buns
are warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, spread the @Mayonnaise{2%tbsp} on the bun bases and the
@Onion Marmalade{30%grams} on the bun lids. Top the bases with some
@Wild Rocket{20%grams} and a cheesy veggie burger, then sandwich shut with the
bun lids.

Add the remaining rocket to the bowl of tomatoes and toss to coat in the
dressing.

Serve your burgers with the chips and salad alongside.

Enjoy!